ybe 99? Then, there's that rule about not placing the test in the same library package just to access it, which my bridge document says signals a violation. So, could renaming to `SecureCallerAccess` help? But, I need to explore options further.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining class loading issues**\\n\\nI'm considering if I could call the cache twice to exercise the path, but that's not needed since the call sites only occur on the first call. I see a potential issue with the active class, `SecureCaller$2.run`, and its anonymous privileged action. In the test source, `SecureCallerAccess` is in the same package, but since the test output precedes the dependency, will the classloader try to load `SecureCaller` from the test output? If not found, it falls back to the dependency. I need to keep exploring this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing native image behavior**\\n\\nI'm looking into how native images interact with `ClassLoader#defineClass`. Our test resource is included, likely due to the metadata resource condition being type-reached from the library, which is good. However, I'm pondering whether the native image might initialize `SecureCaller` during build time because of some resource or condition. But, actually, if the class is initialized at build time through analysis, `loadBytecode` would read the resource at that point and store the bytes. I'm really contemplating this detail!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_h0dYcd9dA11ob1FpXY77mu7w|fc_04c559f649f1dcb40169f8057ee2c081a3909cebc55b567140", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/resources:~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/666c2b4265b9280a2a9316ecfc902716676177c1/htmlunit-core-js-2.70.0.jar net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.SecureCallerImpl 2>/dev/null || true"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "mod